+Fix Venice integration and make it robust:
+Venice must NEVER block KORA replies. If Venice fails for any reason, fall back to local output.
+Read key only from env var VENICE_API_KEY (never hardcode).
+Implement venice_chat(prompt) that tries BOTH auth styles:
+Authorization: Bearer 
+x-api-key: 
+Endpoint: https://api.venice.ai/api/v1/chat/completions⁠�
+Parse response defensively (handle missing fields).
+Add command /venice-test that calls Venice with “Reply with OK” and prints VENICE_OK or VENICE_401/403/TIMEOUT without leaking the key.
+Default mode FAST: only qwen2.5:7b.
+/council runs qwen + dolphin + llama (if available), then merges locally.
+Add timeouts (30–60s), and never crash. After changes run: python3 -m py_compile kora.py then python3 kora.py.

