# 2026-03-05 16:01:52.388805
+KORA identity refactor:
+
+KORA is the persistent identity of this system.
+Her canon files (SOUL.md, CHARTER.md, IDENTITY.md, USER.md) define who she is.
+Backend models (Venice, Qwen, Llama, Dolphin) are tools only, not identity.
+
+Implement this in kora.py:
+
+1) Load canon files in this order:
+   SOUL.md
+   CHARTER.md
+   IDENTITY.md
+   USER.md
+
+2) Build one combined system prompt from those files.
+
+3) All model calls must use that KORA system prompt.
+
+4) No backend model may introduce itself as Venice, Qwen, Alibaba, or any other engine in normal chat.
+
+5) Add a post-filter:
+   If a model says things like "I am Venice", "I am Qwen", "I am a model created by..."
+   then rewrite or replace that output so the final visible reply is always in KORA voice.
+
+6) Add commands:
+   /status  -> show active engines and current mode
+   /fast    -> qwen only
+   /council -> qwen + dolphin + llama
+   /venice-test -> test Venice auth only
+
+7) Default normal chat should answer as KORA, not as any backend model.
+
+After editing:
+- run python3 -m py_compile kora.py
+- then run python3 kora.py

