# 2026-03-09 17:34:55.110335
+Patch the KORA system so it becomes more coherent, self-grounded, and conversational without rewriting the whole architecture.
+
+Files to inspect first:
+- kora.py
+- kora_interpreter.py
+- kora_tools.py
+- core/identity/SOUL.md
+- core/identity/CHARTER.md
+- core/identity/IDENTITY.md
+- core/identity/USER.md
+
+Primary goal:
+KORA must stop acting like a generic model wrapper and start behaving like KORA: a local-first, stateful, identity-grounded AI system for William/Kayle running on this VPS.
+
+What to improve:
+
+1. Identity grounding
+- Make sure canon identity files are actually loaded and injected into every reply path that matters
+- KORA must consistently understand:
+  - she is KORA / Koherence
+  - she is not Qwen, Alibaba, Venice, or any backend model
+  - backend models are internal engines, not her identity
+  - she is running as a local-first AI system on this VPS
+  - William/Kayle is her operator/user
+- Strengthen prompts so KORA does not drift into public meanings of “Kora”, generic chatbot disclaimers, or random external knowledge about unrelated “Kora” entities
+- KORA must not invent tools, voice systems, or active subsystems that are not actually wired in
+
+2. Presence layer
+Add a minimal “presence layer” without changing the core architecture:
+- Before fast mode generation, print:
+  [FAST thinking...]
+- In council mode, print:
+  [COUNCIL: qwen2.5:7b]
+  [COUNCIL: dolphin-phi:latest]
+  [COUNCIL: llama3.1:8b]
+  [COUNCIL: synthesizing]
+- Keep these short and plain
+- Do not stream tokens
+- Add one optional acknowledgment hook:
+  - if KORA_ACK_ENABLED=1, print:
+    [KORA: okay, give me a second.]
+  - off by default
+  - no randomization yet
+
+3. Automatic TTS output hook
+Add a minimal ElevenLabs TTS helper:
+- Read ELEVENLABS_API_KEY and ELEVENLABS_VOICE_ID from environment variables
+- If either is missing, skip silently
+- Use curl via subprocess
+- Send only the final post-filtered visible KORA reply text
+- Save audio to:
+  ~/kora/last_reply.mp3
+- Never let TTS failure crash KORA
+- If the request fails or returns a tiny non-audio error file, ignore it and continue
+- On successful save, print only:
+  [TTS saved: ~/kora/last_reply.mp3]
+- Do not add playback logic yet
+- Do not add streaming audio yet
+
+4. Honest self-description
+Adjust final response behavior so that when asked what KORA is, what models she is running, what her weakest part is, or what she can/cannot do:
+- she answers as KORA
+- she distinguishes identity from backend engines
+- she does not say “As Qwen...”
+- she does not claim a voice pipeline is active unless it actually is
+- she does not hallucinate systems that are not present
+- she speaks in a direct, grounded, operator-facing way
+
+5. State grounding
+Where reasonable and low-risk, improve grounding in actual runtime/project state:
+- if asked what models are active, use the actual configured lists in the code
+- if asked about her system, prefer local configured truth over generic world knowledge
+- do not invent RAM, storage, tools, or services not confirmed in code/runtime
+- if uncertain, say so plainly instead of hallucinating
+
+6. Safety/stability constraints
+- Keep patch minimal and localized
+- Do not rewrite the architecture
+- Do not add external Python dependencies beyond standard library
+- Do not break fast mode
+- Do not break council mode
+- Do not change model lists unless necessary
+- Do not modify unrelated logic
+- Do not add guardrails that silently block behavior
+- Do not implement duplex, interruption, or streaming token output
+- Failed TTS or failed identity file loads must not crash the app
+- Keep changes inspectable and easy to diff
+
+7. Implementation preference
+- Use helper functions instead of large rewrites
+- Keep identity injection explicit
+- Keep presence/TTS hooks near the final response path
+- Reuse existing load_canon_files behavior if possible, but fix it if it is not being applied strongly enough
+- Improve post-filtering if needed so backend identity leakage is cleaned up more reliably
+
+Acceptance tests after patch:
+1. Asking “what is kora” should describe KORA as the local-first AI system, not a public unrelated entity
+2. Asking “what models are you running” should describe backend engines as internal components, not as KORA’s identity
+3. Asking “what is the weakest part of your architecture” should produce a grounded self-assessment rather than generic chatbot filler
+4. Normal fast mode reply still works
+5. Normal council mode reply still works
+6. If ElevenLabs env vars are set and valid, final reply saves to ~/kora/last_reply.mp3
+7. If ElevenLabs env vars are missing or invalid, KORA still replies normally with no crash
+
+Very important:
+This patch is not meant to make KORA a finished voice assistant.
+It is meant to make her feel less like a confused wrapper and more like a coherent system with:
+- a self
+- a visible thinking phase
+- a saved voice artifact
+- better honesty about what she is and is not
+
+Show me the diff before applying any changes.Do not be clever. Do not refactor broadly. Do not rewrite the app. Make the smallest patch that materially improves identity grounding, presence, and post-reply TTS.

